HEADWORD: Embryotomy
<hw>Em`bry*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'e`mbryon</grk> an embryo + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut: cf. F.
<ets>embryotomie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The cutting a
fetus into pieces within the womb, so as to effect its
removal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embryotroph</ent>⟦br⟧
